2000km regards in YouTube/FB!

That misery lasted for three days on the road, five days total. Now recovering in Chisinau, enjoying my antibiotics. “Countries” I was talking about: South Ossetia, Abkhazia and Nagorno-Karabakh.

Ouch. Hang in there and enjoy the break!

When you start resting your eyes for more than 3s while cycling, it’s time to do something about it. Maybe these antibiotics will kill the virus I’ve had for 5 days now. [edit: nasty diarrhea!] Ukraine f*ked up us both properly. Fellow cyclists, do yourself a favour and maybe not go there.

#moldova

Antibiotics to fight a virus? I’m not a doctor, but I think they only treat bacterial infections.
@kartsakoira meant diarrhea lol!
@tourdeteemu So standup pedaling it is. :D
I had same problem when i was in ukrain.
There has been sand/tiny rocks inside my rear wheel during the last two flats. Maybe this is the reason? Well, going to the nearest bike shop anyways.
And you did not check that before 😂
@sami_supersankari I think I got it during emergency breaking when my tube exploded.. Two tubes ago.

That’s it. Going tubeless. Next bike shop in 180km. Perkele.
